===Etymology===
From {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*grwaŋ||village; crossroads}} (STEDT). Cognate with {{cog|bo|གྲོང||house; village; town}}. {{ncog|okz|កុរុង|tr=kuruṅ|t=to rule; ruler; king}} (whence {{ncog|km|ក្រុង}} and {{ncog|th|กรุง}}) is probably unrelated ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

Wu {{zh-l|弄|tr=lon|alley}} and Jin {{zh-l|黑浪|tr=heh4 lon2|hutong}} are dialectal variants which support the Old Chinese ''*gr-'' initial cluster of {{och-l|巷}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}). Compare also {{zh-l|衚衕|hutong}}.

